.TH XIL\-CLEANUP "1" "2026\-04\-05" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-cleanup
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-cleanup
[-h] [--episode TAG] [--show SHOW] [--parsed PATH] [--stems DIR] [--dry-run]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove stale stems that no longer match the current parsed script.  Use \-\-dry\-run first to review what would be deleted.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-episode\fR \fI\,TAG\/\fR
Episode tag (e.g. S02E03); derives \-\-parsed and \-\-stems

.TP
\fB\-\-show\fR \fI\,SHOW\/\fR
Show name override (default: from project.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-parsed\fR \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Parsed script JSON (overrides \-\-episode)

.TP
\fB\-\-stems\fR \fI\,DIR\/\fR
Stems directory (overrides \-\-episode)

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
List stale stems without deleting them

